The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Metro | The City Diary
                                                                            Wednesday , November 11 , 2009                                                                                                                                                                                            The City Diary
                Two homemakers were found hanging in their houses on Tuesday. Sheila Biswas, 40, was found hanging in her Jagaddal house. Her husband Asish Biswas, a constable at South Port police station, was arrested for allegedly abetting her suicide. Cops said Sheilas brother had accused her in-laws of torturing her mentally because the couple did not have a child. Minakshi Das, 19, was found hanging in her Kalibagan house. Her husband Anindya was arrested after Minakshis brother accused him of torturing her for dowry.     Two persons died and four children were injured in three mishaps in the city on Tuesday. Sambhu Saha, 43, died after an unidentified vehicle hit him on Jessore Road near gate No. 2 of the airport. Bhola Rajak, 60, a footpath dweller was knocked down by a lorry in Chitpur. He was declared dead at RG Kar Hospital. Four girls of classes I and II sustained minor injuries after a school van collided with a taxi at Tollygunge Phari.    The auditions for TV talent hunt Dance India Dance will take place on Wednesday. Shortlisted candidates will have to report at the venue, Swabhumi, at 7am.                                                                                                                                                                
